OL,6,F"I'd like to thank the victim for her
OL,7,Fincredible bravery through reporting
OL,8,Fthe incident and through what must
OL,9,Fhave been a really difficult trial,
OL,10,Freliving a traumatic experience.
OL,11,FWithout her continued assistance, the
OL,12,Foutcome would not have been possible.
OL,14,F"We would encourage anyone who has
OL,15,Fbeen the victim of a sexual assault to
OL,16,Fplease report it, do not suffer alone.
OL,18,F"We understand it can be difficult.
OL,19,FYou might not be completely sure what
OL,20,Fhappened or how to talk about it.
